TEXT -272 240 Left 2 ;.ac dec 1k 10 100k
TEXT 120 -512 Left 2 ;This is a bridged T oscillator as used by moritz klein in the mki es hihat. \nR1 is tunable and changes both the center frequency and the Q factor.\nR1 varies from 4.7k to 14.7k with center from 4.4kHz to 7.7kHz
TEXT 240 -568 Left 4 ;BRIDGED T FILTER BANDPASS
TEXT 1672 -288 Left 4 ;BIQUAD/STATE VARIABLE BANDPASS
TEXT 1544 -232 Left 2 ;This emulates the same base frequency response and Q factor but allows for independent \ncontrol of Q and center frequency. Adjust R4 and R5 in conjuction with one another for freq.\nR8 and R9 can be altered to change the Q factor and gain.
TEXT 3120 -424 Left 4 ;OTA STATE VARIABLE BANDPASS
TEXT 3008 -352 Left 2 ;Reimplementing with OTAs for better tuning. Reference circuit for state variable is used from \nLM13700 datasheet
TEXT -272 272 Left 2 !.lib lm13700.sub
TEXT -272 392 Left 2 !.tran 0.1
TEXT 3648 -568 Left 2 ;.step param X -5 5 1
